## independent claim 1 (method)

```
1. A method for [technical field], comprising:

   a) [first step/element];

   b) [second step/element]; and

   c) [third step/element],

   wherein [distinguishing limitation].
```

**novelty basis**: <!-- what makes this claim novel over prior art? -->



---

## dependent claims (method)

```
2. The method of claim 1, wherein [narrowing limitation].

3. The method of claim 1, wherein [alternative limitation].

4. The method of claim 2, further comprising [additional step].
```

---

## independent claim 5 (system)

```
5. A system for [technical field], comprising:

   a processor configured to:
     i) [first function];
     ii) [second function]; and
     iii) [third function]; and

   a memory storing instructions that, when executed, cause the processor to perform the functions.
```

**novelty basis**:



---

## dependent claims (system)

```
6. The system of claim 5, wherein [narrowing limitation].

7. The system of claim 5, further comprising [additional component].
```

